th%3D%5C%22696%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20former%20Securities%20and%20Exchange%20Commission%20operations%20center%20before%20its%20transformation%20into%20a%20spa.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f793f8781926001911b4aa%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22522%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20former%20Securities%20and%20Exchange%20Commission%20operations%20center%20before%20its%20transformation%20into%20a%20spa.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Stephanie%20Chon%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EStephanie%20Chon's%20father%2C%20Steve%20Chon%20%E2%80%94%20also%20known%20as%20the%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbes.com%2Fsites%2Fgracechung%2F2014%2F12%2F04%2Fqueens-spa-king-tries-asian-concept-in-manhattan%2F%3Fsh%3D210be39f722b%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EQueens%20spa%20king%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20owns%20the%20C.Castle%20Group%2C%20which%20operates%20multiple%20spas%2C%20including%20a%20popular%20Korean%20spa%20in%20Queens%2C%20New%20York%2C%20called%20Spa%20Castle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESteve%20and%20Stephanie%20Chon%2C%20who%20is%20C.Castle's%20chief%20operating%20officer%2C%20and%20Steve's%20brothers%2C%20who%20were%20coowners%20of%20C.Castle%2C%20were%20all%20indicted%20on%20criminal%20tax-fraud%20charges%20in%202017.%20The%20state%20charges%20against%20Steve%20and%20Stephanie%20were%20later%20dropped%2C%20while%20Steve's%20brother%2C%20Daniel%20Chon%2C%20pleaded%20guilty.%20Steve%20Chon%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fopa%2Fpr%2Fspa-owner-pleads-guilty-payroll-tax-crimes%5C%22%3Epleaded%20guilty%20to%20federal%20tax-evasion%3C%2Fa%3E%20charges%20in%202022.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Chons%20were%20about%20to%20close%20on%20a%20property%20near%20the%20SEC%20building%20in%202015%20when%20they%20were%20approached%20by%20the%20SEC%20building's%20owner%2C%20who%20was%20looking%20to%20sell.%20The%20building%20had%20been%20vacant%20since