er%2C%20withdrew%20an%20application%20because%20the%20job%20didn't%20allow%20hybrid%20work.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20said%20she%20was%20%26quot%3Bdeflated%26quot%3B%20because%20she%20couldn't%20make%20the%20job%20work%20around%20childcare.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20single%20mother%20said%20companies%20should%20trust%20employees%20to%20balance%20their%20career%20and%20home%20life.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20transcribed%20conversation%20with%20Kimberley%20Whitaker%2C%20a%20lawyer%20in%20London.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20had%20my%20daughter%20in%202019%2C%20I%20needed%20to%20work%20out%20how%20on%20earth%20I%20was%20going%20to%20be%20both%20a%20corporate%20lawyer%20and%20a%20single%20mother.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20fortunate%20because%20working%20became%20more%20flexible%20after%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20hit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20applied%20for%20a%20role%20as%20general%20counsel%2C%20the%20head%20lawyer%20who's%20expected%20to%20advise%20on%20all%20issues%20for%20an%20organization%2C%20for%20HealthHero%2C%20I%20was%20candid%20in%20my%20interview%20that%20I%20never%20wanted%20to%20be%20in%20the%20office%20more%20than%20a%20couple%20of%20days%20a%20week.%20I%20also%20said%20I%20would%20need%20to%20leave%20work%20at%205%3A30%20p.m.%20if%20I%20was%20working%20from%20home%20and%205%20p.m.%20if%20I%20was%20in%20the%20office%20so%20I%20could%20collect%20my%20daughter%20from%20nursery.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20told%20me%20that%20as%20long%20as%20I%20could%20get%20the%20job%20done%2C%20it%20was%20up%20to%20me%20how%20I%20did%20it.%20I%20felt%20very%20empowered%20by%20that.%20Without%20that%20flexibility%2C%20I'm%20not%20sure%20I%20would've%20been%20able%20to%20do%20a%20general-counsel%20role.%20As%20a%20single%20mum%20to%20a%20little%20one%2C%20it%20was%20worrying%20because%20I%20used%20to%20be%20in%20the%20office%20at%20all%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESomeone%20once%20told%20me%20that%20as%20a%20parent%2C%20I%20wouldn't%20have%20the%20same%20drives%20and%20ambitions%20as%20I%20did%20before.%20That%20is%20untrue.%20I%20had%20the%20same%20ambition%20%E2%80%94%20but%20I%20worried%20about%20how%20I%20was%20going%20to%20make%20it%20work%20with%20additional%20responsibilities%20in%20my%20life%20and%20with%20a%20social%20structure%20that%20didn't%20seem%20to%20support%20parents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20hybrid%20model%20worked%20best%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20like%20the%20hybrid%20model%20because%20it's%20nice%20to%20see%20people%20in%20the%20office%2C%20and%20conversations%20are%20best%20face-to-face.%20I%20think%20some%20mandated%20office%20time%20works%20well%20for%20the%20legal%20sector.%20I%20learned%20so%20much%20from%20watching%20more-senior%20lawyers%20throughout%20my%20career.%20I%20think%20that's%20valuable%20for%20trainee%20and%20junior%20lawyers.%20But%20five%20days%20in%20the%20office%20isn't%20necessary%20for%20a%20high-performing%20culture%20and%20building%20bonds%20with%20colleagues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20days%20I%20went%20into%20the%20office%2C%20which%20was%20about%20twice%20a%20week%20from%20September%202022%2C%20I'd%20be%20up%20at%205%3A15%20a.m.%20to%20work%20out%20and%20shower%20before%20my%20daughter%20woke%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20the%20second%20I%20woke%20up%2C%20I%20felt%20like%20I%20was%20rushing.%20Colleagues%20might%20see%20me%20eat%20breakfast%20at%20my%20desk%20at%209%20a.m.%20and%20rush%20out%20of%20the%20office%20at%205%20p.m.%2C%20but%20they%20didn't%20know%20I'd%20already%20been%20up%20for%20four%20hours%20by%20the%20time%20I%20had%20that%20first%20coffee%20and%20porridge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20withdrew%20a%20job%20application%20because%20the%20employer%20mandated%205%20days%20in%20the%20office%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20left%20my%20job%20at%20HealthHero%20in%20May%20to%20spend%20the%20summer%20with%20my%20daughter%20before%20she%20started%20school.%20I've%20been%20looking%20for%20a%20job%20over%20the%20past%20month%20or%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20applied%20for%20another%20general-counsel%20role%20in%20July.%20There%20are%20never%20that%20many%20available.%20To%20find%20one%20that%2C%20on%20paper%2C%20matched%20so%20much%20of%20what%20I%20was%20looking%20for%20was%20hugely%20exciting.%20During%20my%20interview%2C%20the%20employer%20said%20that%20it%20required%20five%20days%20a%20week%20in%20the%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20surprised%20and%20deflated.%20It%20was%20an%20outdated%20approach%2C%20given%20the%20changes%20we've%20seen%20since%20COVID-19%20affected%20our%20working%20practices.%20I%20was%20disappointed%20that%20this%20job%20probably%20wouldn't%20work%20for%20me.%20It%20would%20mean%20breakfast%20club%20and%20after-school%20club%20every%20day%20for%20my%20daughter%20and%20maybe%20additional%20care%20after%20evening%20wraparound%20care%20%E2%80%94%20I%20would%20barely%20see%20her%20in%20the%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESix%20weeks%20later%2C%20I%20was%20told%20the%20company%20was%20delighted%20with%20my%20interview%20and%20wanted%20to%20proceed%20to%20the%20next%20interview%20in%20the%20application%20process.%20I%20turned%20it%20down.%20I%20said%20that%20five%20days%20wouldn't%20work%20for%20me%20or%20for%20anyone%20with%20caring%20responsibilities%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20I%20thought%20it%20was%20important%20to%20allow%20flexibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20would've%20liked%20to%20have%20taken%20the%20role%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20role%20were%20hybrid%2C%20I%20would%20have%20continued%20with%20the%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWalking%20away%20was%20a%20bit%20scary%2C%20both%20because%20of%20the%20type%20of%20role%20it%20was%20and%20because%20it%20would%20have%20been%20reassuring%20to%20have%20something%20lined%20up%20to%20start%20after%20my%20daughter%20was%20in%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20briefly%20wondered%20whether%20I%20should%20keep%20myself%20in%20the%20running%20but%20decided%20that%20it%20was%20easier%20to%20walk%20away%20before%20getting%20an%20offer.%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20be%20tempted%20to%20accept%20something%20that%20wasn't%20going%20to%20work%20in%20my%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EFlexibility%20is%20key%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20isn't%20just%20about%20the%20five%20days%20in%20the%20office%20but%20also%20about%20what%20that%20represents%3A%20a%20lack%20of%20recognition%20that%20flexibility%20is%20needed%20by%20some%20and%20can%20work%20for%20companies%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECountless%20employers%20have%20moved%20on%20from%20that%20and%20realize%20that%20there's%20a%20balance%20between%20being%20in%20the%20office%20and%20building%20relationships%20with%20colleagues%2C%20and%20having%20flexibility%20that%20makes%20work-life%20balance%20better.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20plan%20is%20for%20days%20I'm%20working%20%E2%80%94%20both%20from%20home%20and%20in%20the%20office%20%E2%80%94%20to%20have%20childcare%20covered%20until%206%20p.m.%2C%20through%20after-school%20club%2C%20or%20help%20from%20my%20dad%20or%20friends.%20When%20I%20go%20into%20the%20office%2C%20I'd%20need%20my%20daughter%20to%20go%20to%20breakfast%20club%20so%20I%20could%20get%20in%20on%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'd%20be%20open%20to%20working%20fully%20remote%20but%20one%20or%20two%20days%20in%20the%20office%20would%20be%20perfect.%20I%20wouldn't%20want%20to%20work%20from%20the%20office%20more%20than%20three%20days%20a%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20it's%20important%20for%20employers%20to%20trust%20employees%20to%20make%20things%20work%20in%20our%20lives.%20I%20want%20an%20interesting%2C%20varied%2C%20and%20exciting%20career%2C%20but%20I%20also%20want%20to%20raise%20my%20daughter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fturned-down-job-interview-because-of-return-to-office-rto-2023-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694082245000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f855caa35dd100195ee68e%3Fformat%3Dj