href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Fnews.release%2Fbrs1.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20at%20least%203%25%20of%20the%20workforce%20is%20working%20completely%20remotely%20as%20of%20September%2030%2C%202022.%20That%20means%20about%2011.1%25%20of%20companies%20across%20the%20country%20are%20allowing%20it%20%E2%80%94%20a%20bump%20from%2010.3%25%20in%202021.%20A%20separate%20Government%20Accountability%20Office%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gao.gov%2Fproducts%2Fgao-23-105999%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanalysis%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20American%20Community%20Survey%20data%20found%20that%20in%202021%2C%20about%2018%25%20of%20workers%20primarily%20worked%20from%20home%20during%20the%20week.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20even%20as%20the%20number%20of%20firms%20offering%20any%20form%20of%20telework%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Fnews.release%2Fbrs1.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehas%20plummeted%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20when%20and%20where%20of%20work%20remains%20a%20constant%20push%20and%20pull.%20Several%20workers%20Insider%20spoke%20to%20said%20they've%20left%20jobs%20%E2%80%94%20and%20even%20took%20pay%20cuts%20%E2%80%94%20to%20stay%20at%20home.%20As%20office%20mandates%20stack%20up%2C%20it's%20a%20battle%20that's%20far%20from%20over.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20who%20are%20the%20remote%20workers%20of%20America%3F%20They're%20likely%20to%20be%20more%20educated%2C%20run%20errands%20during%20the%20day%2C%20and%20are%20willing%20to%20do%20whatever%20it%20takes%20to%20stay%20at%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERemote%20workers%20save%20up%20to%2080%20minutes%20a%20day%20by%20not%20going%20into%20the%20office%20%E2%80%94%20and%20many%20use%20it%20to%20work%20more.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225546%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22doing%20a%20face%20mask%20during%20work%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F641488ce5f4f5400191a164d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224160%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERemote%20workers%20are%20doing%20anything%20but%20work%20in%20the%20afternoons.%3Cp%3EElena%20Noviello%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20there's%20a%20stereotype%20that%20remote%20employees%20work%20less%2C%20many%20are%20putting%20their%20extra%20time%20into%20working%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERemote%20workers%20in%20the%20US%20rack%20up%2055%20minutes%20a%20day%20in%20%26quot%3Btime%20savings%26quot%3B%20from%20being%20at%20home%20and%20cutting%20out%20commuting%20and%20other%20activities%20like%20grooming%2C%20the%20researchers%20Cevat%20Giray%20Aksoy%2C%20Jose%20Maria%20Barrero%2C%20Nicholas%20Bloom%2C%20Steven%20J.%20Davis%2C%20Mathias%20Dolls%2C%20and%20Pablo%20Zarate%20found%20in%20their%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbfi.uchicago.edu%2Finsight%2Fresearch-summary%2Ftime-savings-when-working-from-home%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanalysis%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20Global%20Survey%20of%20Working%20Arrangements.%20Across%20the%20world%2C%20younger%20workers%20are%20likely%20to%20reap%20the%20most%20time%20savings%2C%20with%20remote%20workers%20under%20the%20age%20of%2030%20getting%20back%20nearly%2080%20minutes%20a%20day.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20US%2C%20workers%20are%20putting%2042%25%20of%20that%20extra%20time%20toward%20working.%20And%20that's%20fairly%20consistent%20across%20the%20globe%2C%20with%2040%25%20of%20time%20savings%20spent%20on%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFelicia%2C%20a%2053-year-old%20administrator%20in%20Arizona%20who%20quit%20her%20six-figure%20job%20over%20a%20return-to-office%20push%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-work-return-to-office-quit-job-micromanager-boss-salary-2023-4%5C%22%3Epreviously%20told%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20she%20found%20she%20%26quot%3Bgot%20a%20lot%20more%20work%20done%26quot%3B%20when%20she%20was%20at%20home.%20When%20she%20went%20into%20the%20office%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20going%20home%20and%20working%20four%20hours%20because%20I%20couldn't%20get%20the%20work%20done%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThey%20earn%20more%2C%20are%20more%20educated%2C%20and%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20work%20in%20tech%20or%20similar%20industries.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227285%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22remote%20work%20with%20kid%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F640f611ea3b2a10018b2b5d4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225464%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EGetty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EA%20good%20rule%20of%20thumb%20for%20access%20to%20remote%20work%3A%20If%20you%20make%20more%20money%2C%20you're%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20at%20home.%20The%20GAO%20analysis%20of%20American%20Time%20Use%20Survey%20data%20found%20that%20in%202021%2C%20nearly%2060%25%20of%20workers%20in%20the%20top%2025%25%20of%20earners%20did%20some%20work%20from%20home.%20In%20comparison%2C%20about%2015%25%20of%20workers%20in%20the%20bottom%20quartile%20of%20earners%20did%20some%20work%20from%20home.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwfhresearch.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2FWFHResearch_updates_September2023.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAugust%202023%20iteration%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20Survey%20of%20Working%20Arrangements%20and%20Attitudes%20found%20that%20about%2013%25%20of%2030-%20to%2039-year-olds%20and%2050-%20to%2064-year-olds%20work%20remotely%20full%20time%2C%20the%20two%20age%20groups%20with%20the%20highest%20percentage%20of%20full-time%20remote%20workers.%20However%2C%2066%25%20of%2050-%20to%2064-year-olds%20worked%20fully%20on-site%2C%20the%20highest%20percentage%20among%20the%20age%20groups%2C%20followed%20by%20about%2060%25%20of%2020-%20to%2029-year-olds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F6iOdS%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Establishments%20with%20all%20employees%20teleworking%20all%20of%20the%20time%20by%20industry%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22707%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20GAO%2C%20women%20were%20more%20likely%20to%20primarily%20work%20from%20home%20than%20men.%20About%2028%25%20of%20Asian%20Americans%20worked%20primarily%20from%20home%2C%20the%20highest%20percentage%20among%20Americans%20of%20different%20races%2C%20compared%20to%2019%25%20of%20white%20Americans%20and%2015%25%20of%20Black%20Americans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20Americans%20working%20from%20home%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20hold%20college%20degrees.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nber.org%2Fsystem%2Ffiles%2Fworking_papers%2Fw31439%2Fw31439.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EResearch%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20Washington%20State%20University%20economist%20Benjamin%20Cowan%20found%20that%20college%20graduates%20spent%20more%20time%20working%20from%20home%20compared%20to%20non-college%20graduates.%20In%20the%20%26quot%3Bpost-pandemic%20era%26quot%3B%20of%20August%202021%20through%20December%202022%2C%20the%20amount%20of%20time%20college%20graduates%20spent%20working%20at%20home%20increased%20by%2078%20minutes%20compared%20to%202015%20through%202019%20levels%2C%20according%20to%20Cowan's%20analysis%20of%20Census%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20vast%20majority%20of%20jobs%20that%20are%20easy%20to%20transition%20to%20home%20work%20are%20held%20by%20highly%20educated%20college-graduate%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20Cowan%20told%20Insider.%20Not%20only%20are%20college%20graduates%20more%20likely%20to%20work%20from%20home%2C%20according%20to%20Cowan%2C%20but%20%26quot%3Bit's%20one%20of%20the%20most%20important%20predictors%20of%20not%20only%20who%20works%20from%20home%2C%20full%20stop%2C%20but%20who%20has%20transitioned%20to%20more%20home%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20remote%20workers%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20found%20in%20white-collar%2C%20knowledge%20positions%20such%20as%20the%20information%20sector%2C%20which%20includes%20tech%2C%20digital-publishing%2C%20and%20data-processing%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERemote%20workers%20are%20living%20a%20little%20like%20college%20students.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226399%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22remote%20work%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F60bf9ae5a7202d0018b8dbb9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224800%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EJohner%20Images%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWorking%20from%20home%20means%20that%20breaks%20aren't%20just%20reserved%20for%20scrolling%20on%20your%20phone%20or%20chatting%20with%20a%20coworker.%20Remote%20workers%20are%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Fhow-workers-really-spend-their-days-d06c8f5f%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eusing%20their%20downtime%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20exercise%2C%20run%20errands%2C%20do%20chores%2C%20or%20read.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20way%20I%20see%20it%20is%20work%20from%20home%20is%20much%20more%20like%20the%20student%20lifestyle%2C%26quot%3B%20Nick%20Bloom%2C%20a%20Stanford%20economist%20who%20helped%20spearhead%20research%20on%20work-from-home%20time%20use%2C%20previously%20told%20Insider.%20It%20means%20that%20remote%20workers%20aren't%20necessarily%20working%20straight%20through%20from%20nine-to-five%2C%20but%20knocking%20out%20chores%20in%20the%20afternoon%20and%20logging%20back%20on%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20Bloom%20and%20his%20researchers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-jobs-schedule-errands-leisure-during-work-hours-2023-3%5C%22%3Efound%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20with%20the%20rise%20of%20remote%20work%2C%20more%20people%20were%20hitting%20the%20golf%20course%20on%20weekday%20afternoons%2C%20especially%20on%20Wednesdays%20at%204%20p.m.%3B%20the%20researchers%20said%20that%20time%20is%20probably%20being%20utilized%20for%20other%20leisure%20activities%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20led%20to%20what%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Fwork-office-coworkers-schedule-meetings-2af3f9b0%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%3C%2Fa%3E%20called%20a%20work%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femployees-leaving-early-finishing-work-at-night-triple-peak-day-2023-7%5C%22%3Edead%20zone%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20the%20hours%20between%204%20p.m.%20and%206%20p.m%2C%20when%20workers%20log%20off%20early%20to%20pick%20up%20their%20kids%20and%20complete%20other%20errands%20and%20then%20log%20back%20on%20later%20in%20the%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERemote%20workers%20are%20willing%20to%20do%20whatever%20it%20takes%20to%20stay%20remote%20%E2%80%94%20including%20take%20a%20pay%20cut.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221892%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20wearing%20a%20blue%20beanie%20hat%2C%20a%20mask%2C%20and%20a%20colorful%20jacket%20reads%20a%20book%20on%20his%20commute%20in%20the%20New%20York%20Subway.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F63e228c296242f0019e7b4fb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221419%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20man%20reads%20a%20book%20during%20an%20uptown%20subway%20ride%20January%2013%2C%202022%20in%20New%20York%20City.%3Cp%3ERobert%20Nickelsberg%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EStaying%20at%20home%20is%20valuable%20to%20workers%20%E2%80%94%20so%20valuable%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20they're%20willing%20to%20lose%20out%20on%20pay%20to%20work%20remotely.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJay%2C%20an%20elder%20millennial%2C%20took%20a%20%2435%2C000%20pay%20cut%20and%20step%20down%20in%20seniority%20to%20live%20and%20work%20where%20he%20wanted%20to.%20In%20his%20old%20position%2C%20he%20had%20to%20live%20closer%20to%20the%20office%2C%20despite%20working%20remotely.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20just%20kind%20of%20wish%20that%20employers%20would%20realize%20that%20talent%20doesn't%20just%20live%20within%20a%20certain%20radius%20of%20an%20office%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeet-elder-millennial-who-took-35000-pay-cut-stay-remote-2023-8%5C%22%3Etold%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Jay%20is%20not%20alone%3A%2055%25%20of%20188%20fully%20remote%20workers%20surveyed%20by%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fbusiness%2F2023%2F05%2F23%2Fpost-poll-remote-work-hybrid-future%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Washington%20Post%20and%20Ipsos%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-remote-workers-would-take-pay-cut-to-keep-wfh-2023-5%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20they'd%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-work-from-home-jobs-millennial-pay-cut-great-resignation-2022-6%5C%22%3Etake%20a%20lower-paying%20job%20if%20it%20meant%20they%20could%20stay%20at%20home%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20even%20workers%20who%20are%20unhappy%20with%20their%20remote%20roles%20don't%20want%20to%20leave%20because%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-workers-want-work-from-home-benefits-arent-happy-jobs-2023-4%5C%22%3Ethey%20don't%20want%20to%20risk%20giving%20up%20working%20from%20home%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDone%2C%20the%20millennial%20who%20left%20his%20role%20rather%20than%20return%20to%20the%20office%2C%20spent%20five%20months%20without%20a%20job.%20He%20finally%20ended%20up%20in%20a%20role%20that%20paid%20more%2C%20but%20he%20said%20making%20the%20decision%20to%20leave%20was%20one%20of%20the%20scarier%20moments%20in%20his%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20Felicia%2C%20the%20administrator%20who%20left%20a%20six-figure%20job%20because%20of%20her%20company's%20back-to-office%20p