com%2F64f8c23d8a78400019617a83%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222274%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EGrace%20Mayer%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20pandemic%2C%20when%20wait%20times%20were%20especially%20long%20in%20drive-thru%20lines%20at%20many%20fast-food%20chains%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmcdonalds-menu-items-removed-2020-12%5C%22%3EMcDonald's%20cut%20some%20menu%20items%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20speed%20up%20its%20operations.%20Its%20AI-voice%20powered%20speakers%20in%20the%20drive-thrus%20are%20just%20the%20latest%20innovation%20from%20the%20fast-food%20chain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EChick-fil-A%20has%20also%20said%20it's%20working%20to%20speed%20up%20its%20drive-thrus.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222220%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Chick-Fil-A%20drive%20thru%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F647726cfdf2567001837d001%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221665%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EBrandon%20Bell%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EChick-fil-A%20is%20working%20on%20rolling%20out%20%26quot%3Bexpress%20lanes%2C%26quot%3B%20solely%20for%20customers%20who%20place%20orders%20ahead%20on%20their%20mobile%20app.%20The%20express%20lanes%20would%20be%20designed%20to%20allow%20customers%20to%20breeze%20much%20faster%20through%20the%20drive-thru%20lanes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20restaurant%20is%20also%20opening%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchick-fil-a-drive-thru-only-restaurantphotos-2022-10%5C%22%3Edrive-thru%20only%20locations%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20US%20that%20are%20specifically%20designed%20to%20handle%20high-volume%20drive-thru%20orders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EMy%20experiences%20at%20both%20fast-food%20chains%20showed%20how%20the%20brands%20are%20taking%20different%20routes%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20customer%20service%20in%20their%20drive-thrus.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22mcdonalds%20employee%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f8c2e956f5190019fc4f44%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222254%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20employee%20at%20McDonald's%20hands%20a%20customer%20his%20credit%20card%20and%20receipt%20behind%20a%20special%20piece%20of%20glass%20for%20protection%20after%20taking%20his%20order.%3Cp%3EMichael%20Siluk%2FEducation%20Images%2FUniversal%20Images%20Group%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20I%20preferred%20Chick-fil-A's%20focus%20on%20human%20interaction%2C%20even%20through%20the%20service%20was%20slower.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20nice%20to%20see%20Chick-fil-A%20employees'%20smiles%20and%20hear%20their%20enthusiasm%20for%20helping%20me.%20By%20comparison%2C%20I%20was%20initially%20startled%20to%20hear%20the%20AI%20bot%20at%20the%20McDonald's%20drive-thru.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20sure%20I'll%20get%20used%20to%20AI%20drive-thru%20bots%20as%20more%20chains%20adopt%20them.%20White%20Castle%2C%20Panera%20Bread%2C%20Popeyes%2C%20and%20Taco%20Bell%20are%20among%20the%20many%20chains%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffast-food-chains-like-white-castle-turn-to-voice-bots%3Finline-endstory-related-recommendations%3D%237-popeyes-9%5C%22%3Etesting%20AI-powered%20voice%20technology.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20widespread%20use%20of%20the%20bots%20could%20also%20give%20Chick-fil-A%20a%20leg%20up%20over%20rivals%20for%20customers%20like%20me%20who%20prefer%20face-to-face%20customer%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmcdonalds-vs-chick-fil-a-drive-thru-review-order-wait-2023-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694079000000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f8d92d56f5190019fc67d9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmcdonalds-vs-chick-fil-a-drive-thru-review-order-wait-2023-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22McDonald's%20is%20using%20AI%20voice%20recognition%20to%20take%20orders%2C%20while%20Chick-fil-A%20is%20leaning%20into%20the%20human%20touch%20with%20friendly%20fast-food%20workers.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22gmayer%40insider.com%20(Grace%20Mayer)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmcdonalds-vs-chick-fil-a-drive-thru-review-order-wait-2023-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Meet%20the%20pro-housing%20agitators%20who%20are%20fighting%20to%20bring%20down%20home%20prices%20%E2%80%94%20and%20winning%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20large%20house%20being%20surrounded%20by%20smaller%20homes%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f793761b7ced0019c8909a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EYIMBYs%20want%20to%20solve%20America's%20housing%20crisis%20by%20making%20it%20easier%20to%20build%20homes%20%E2%80%94%20and%20they're%20starting%20to%20notch%20key%20wins%20in%20big%20cities.%3Cp%3ETyler%20Le%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EInside%20the%20fight%20to%20build%20more%20housing%20and%20bring%20down%20home%20prices%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20a%20new%20movement%20sweeping%20America.%20It%20isn't%20selling%20out%20stadiums%20or%20inspiring%20riots%2C%20but%20it%20does%20contain%20a%20simple%20idea%20that%20has%20the%20potential%20to%20radically%20reshape%20our%20economy%3A%20The%20US%20needs%20more%20places%20for%20people%20to%20live.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20adherents%20of%20the%20%26quot%3BYes%20In%20My%20Backyard%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20YIMBY%2C%20movement%20believe%20that%20America's%20housing%20crisis%20comes%20down%20to%20the%20fundamental%20tension%20between%20supply%20and%20demand.%20The%20country%20simply%20doesn't%20have%20enough%20homes%2C%20they%20argue%2C%20so%20people%20are%20forced%20to%20fight%2C%20scrape%2C%20and%20pay%20exorbitant%20prices%20to%20secure%20the%20housing%20that%20is%20available.%20Building%20more%20homes%2C%20or%20%26quot%3Bhousing%20abundance%26quot%3B%20in%20YIMBY%20parlance%2C%20is%20the%20key%20to%20improving%20access%20and%20ensuring%20an%20affordable%20cost%20of%20living.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20the%20belief%20that%20we%20can%20and%20should%20solve%20our%20housing%20crisis%20by%20building%20a%20lot%20more%20housing%2C%20especially%20in%20high%20opportunity%2C%20transit-rich%20neighborhoods%2C%26quot%3B%20Nolan%20Gray%2C%20a%20city%20planner%20and%20research%20director%20for%20California%20YIMBY%2C%20told%20Insider.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYIMBYism%20isn't%20a%20new%20idea%2C%20but%20over%20the%20past%20couple%20of%20years%20it%20has%20started%20to%20notch%20small%20but%20crucial%20victories%20that%20appear%20to%20signal%20that%20the%20movement%20is%20becoming%20more%20broadly%20accepted.%20From%20coast%20to%20coast%2C%20cities%20and%20states%20are%20defying%20the%20dominant%20%26quot%3BNot%20In%20My%20Backyard%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20NIMBY%2C%20ideas%20that%20have%20for%20decades%20dominated%20most%20housing%20discussions.%20YIMBYism%20has%20gained%20traction%20as%20the%20affordability%20crisis%20has%20gotten%20worse.%20Two-thirds%20of%20Americans%20say%20it's%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftoday.yougov.com%2Ftopics%2Feconomy%2Farticles-reports%2F2023%2F07%2F19%2Famericans-say-difficult-find-affordable-housing%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehard%20to%20find%20an%20affordable%20home%3C%2Fa%3E%20where%20they%20live.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Fhomelessness-increasing-united-states-housing-costs-e1990ac7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHomelessness%20is%20on%20the%20rise%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20a%20growing%20share%20of%20Americans%20are%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F01%2F25%2Frealestate%2Frent-burdened-american-households.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erent-burdened%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20can't%20afford%20to%20buy%20a%20home.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20idea%20also%20has%20appeal%20across%20the%20political%20spectrum%3A%20Progressives%20support%20housing%20abundance%20as%20a%20way%20to%20boost%20affordability.%20Conservatives%20and%20libertarians%20see%20it%20as%20a%20way%20to%20get%20rid%20of%20government%20regulation%20and%20empower%20property%20owners.%20If%20the%20movement%20continues%20to%20attract%20followers%20and%20win%20over%20local%2C%20state%2C%20and%20federal%20leaders%2C%20it%20could%20make%20American%20cities%20and%20suburbs%20more%20affordable%20and%20diverse.%20Sonja%20Trauss%2C%20the%20executive%20director%20of%20the%20group%20YIMBY%20Law%2C%20said%20the%20movement%20has%20a%20lot%20left%20to%20accomplish%20and%20the%20anti-building%20NIMBYs%20still%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20political%20power%2C%20but%20the%20future%20appears%20brighter%20than%20ever.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20at%20the%20other%20team's%20touchdown%20line%2C%26quot%3B%20Trauss%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20feel%20like%20they%20have%20shot%20all%20of%20their%20loads.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EIf%20you%20build%20it%20%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20crux%20of%20the%20YIMBY%20plan%20is%20to%20build%20more%20housing%20by%20reducing%20the%20number%20of%20choke%20points%20in%20the%20development%20process.%20Restrictive%20building%20codes%2C%20local%20opposition%2C%20and%20many%20other%20stumbling%20blocks%20can%20downsize%20or%20outright%20prevent%20new%20housing.%20Perhaps%20the%20biggest%20of%20them%20all%20is%20single-family%20zoning.%20And%20while%20California%20still%20has%20some%20of%20the%20highest%20home%20prices%20in%20the%20nation%2C%20it%20was%20a%20fight%20against%20single-family%20zoning%20there%20that%20gave%20birth%20to%20the%20modern%20YIMBY%20movement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20early%202010s%2C%20the%20San%20Francisco%20Bay%20Area%20faced%20a%20rapidly%20worsening%20housing-affordability%20crisis%20sparked%20in%20part%20by%20the%20tech%20boom%2C%20and%20local%20NIMBYs%20were%20stymieing%20much-needed%20construction.%20Trauss%20was%20a%20high-school%20math%20teacher%20in%20San%20Francisco%20when%20she%20began%20noticing%20that%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20she%20knew%20had%20started%20to%20come%20around%20to%20the%20idea%20that%20%26quot%3Bhousing%20is%20good.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20were%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20who%20all%20agreed%20with%20each%20other%2C%20but%20everybody%20thought%20they%20were%20the%20only%20one%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20So%20Trauss%20began%20advocating%20for%20more%20housing%20at%20local%20planning%20meetings%20and%20helped%20start%20the%20YIMBY%20movement.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20main%20targets%20for%20reform%20was%20zoning%20laws%20%E2%80%94%20local%20regulations%20that%20determine%20what%20kind%20of%20buildings%20can%20go%20where.%20Some%20areas%20are%20zoned%20for%20commercial%20buildings%20or%20skyscrapers%2C%20others%20for%20apartment%20buildings%20or%20agricultural%20use.%20Today%2C%20nearly%2075%25%20of%20residentially-zoned%20land%20in%20the%20US%20is%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2Finteractive%2F2019%2F06%2F18%2Fupshot%2Fcities-across-america-question-single-family-zoning.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erestricted%20to%20single-family%20housing%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20detached%20homes%20designed%20for%20one%20family.%20Single-family%20zoning%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jchs.harvard.edu%2Fblog%2Fsingle-family-zoning-can-history-be-reversed%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebecame%20entrenched%20in%20the%20US%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20mid-20th%20century%20as%20white%20localities%20used%20zoning%20laws%20to%20box%20out%20manufacturing%20areas%20and%20prevent%20Black%20families%20from%20moving%20into%20their%20neighborhoods.%20Today%2C%20neighborhoods%20that%20are%20exclusively%20zoned%20for%20single-family%20homes%20still%20reinforce%20racial%20and%20socioeconomic%20segregation%2C%20the%20Urban%20Institute%20found%2C%20as%20they%20tend%20to%20be%20occupied%20by%20whiter%20and%20wealthier%20people%20than%20denser%2C%20multifamily%20housing.%20And%20it%20locks%20lower-income%20people%20of%20color%20out%20of%20the%20opportunities%20for%20upward%20social%20mobility%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0from%20well-funded%20schools%20to%20cleaner%20air%20%E2%80%94%20that%20are%20found%20in%20wealthier%20neighborhoods.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EWe%20can%20and%20should%20solve%20our%20housing%20crisis%20by%20building%20a%20lot%20more%20housing%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20years%20of%20being%20outnumbered%20in%20local%20meetings%2C%20YIMBYs%20began%20using%20the%20same%20local%20organizing%20tactics%20that%20NIMBYs%20pioneered%2C%20Trauss%20said.%20Pro-building%20advocates%20have%20become%20famous%20for%20their%20impassioned%20feuds%20with%20opponents%20on%20Twitter%20and%20in%20community%20meetings.%20They're%20electing%20pro-housing%20lawmakers%20at%20every%20level%20and%20pushing%20them%20to%20pass%20YIMBY%20policies.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20go%20to%20these%20public%20hearings%20that%20maybe%20were%20once%20exclusively%20dominated%20by%20people%20who%20are%20opposing%20anything%20and%20everything%2C%26quot%3B%20Gray%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20now%20you%20have%20a%20few%20people%20show%20up%20saying%2C%20'Hey%2C%20actually%2C%20I'm%20a%20young%20professional%20who%20wants%20to%20be%20able%20to%20stay%20in%20the%20city%20where%20I'm%20from%2C'%20or%20'I'm%20a%20retiree%20who%20wants%20to%20be%20able%20to%20downsize%2C'%20or%20'I'm%20somebody%20who's%20experienced%20homelessness%2C'%20and%20it%20totally%20changes%20the%20tenor%20of%20those%20conversations%20and%20it%20provides%20planning%20conditions%20and%20city%20councils%20cover%20to%20do%20the%20right%20things.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20local%20passion%20eventually%20extended%20to%20the%20state%20level.%20The%20California%20legislature%20has%20passed%20a%20series%20of%20laws%20in%20recent%20years%20that%20allowed%20homeowners%20to%20build%20more%20housing%20on%20their%20property.%20In%202021%2C%20lawmakers%20passed%20Senate%20Bill%209%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0which%20effectively%20banned%20single-family%20zoning%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0a%20%26quot%3Bsymbolic%26quot%3B%20push%20to%20show%20what%20kind%20of%20radical%20efforts%20were%20needed%20to%20quell%20the%20housing%20crisis.%20The%20moves%20have%20had%20a%20substantial%20effect%20on%20local%20policy%3A%20Two-thirds%20of%20zoned%20land%20in%20California%20was%20previously%20restricted%20to%20single-family%20homes%2C%20but%20now%20homeowners%20can%20build%20up%20to%20four%20more%20units%20on%20most%20single%20lots%20across%20the%20state.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESubsequent%20bills%20have%20also%20allowed%20for%20alternative%20types%20of%20housing%20that%20could%20help%20ease%20soaring%20costs.%20For%20instance%2C%20Senate%20Bill%2035%20laid%20out%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcalifornia-affordable-housing-real-estate-ignores-community-input-opposition-2023-8%5C%22%3Erules%20for%20building%20accessory-dwelling%20units%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20smaller%2C%20detached%20homes%20like%20backyard%20%26quot%3Bgranny%20flats.%26quot%3B%20In%202022%2C%20California%20approved%20more%20than%2023%2C000%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fadu-tiny-homes-affordable-housing-california-laws-2023-2%5C%22%3EADU%20permits%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20up%20from%20fewer%20than%205%2C000%20in%202017.%20A%20total%20of%20about%2060%2C000%20new%20accessory-dwelling%20units%20have%20been%20built%20in%20the%20state%20since%202016%20%E2%80%94%20with%20the%20rate%20of%20construction%20growing%20each%20year.%20In%20Los%20Angeles%20County%20alone%20%E2%80%94%20where%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcalifornia-unlivable-nightmare-housing-climate-change-2019-11%5C%22%3Ethe%20housing%20crisis%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20particularly%20severe%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Departments%20of%20Regional%20Planning%20and%20Public%20Works%20approved%20a%20total%20of%202%2C005%20new%20ADUs%20in%202022%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20told%20Insider.%20They've%20made%20up%20nearly%20a%20quarter%20of%20all%20new%20housing%20construction%20in%20the%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20nationwide%20movement%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20San%20Francisco-style%20housing%20crises%20have%20become%20more%20common%20all%20over%20the%20country%2C%20new-wave%20YIMBYism%20has%20also%20spread%20from%20coast%20to%20coast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBefore%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%2C%20I%20had%20to%20justify%20this%20as%20an%20issue%20in%20places%20like%20Florida%20or%20Utah%2C%26quot%3B%20Gray%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20now%20the%20script%20has%20completely%20flipped.%20Folks%20are%20like%2C%20'Oh%2C%20we're%20in%20a%20housing%20crisis%20for%20the%20very%20first%20time.%20What%20are%20you%20all%20doing%20in%20California%3F'%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22People%20spend%20time%20in%20front%20of%20the%20famous%20Victorian%20houses%20called%20'Painted%20Ladies'%20at%20Alamo%20Square%20in%20San%20Francisco%2C%20California%2C%20United%20States%20on%20August%209%2C%202023.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f8a65d99e07a0019e099c4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22853%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGround%20zero%20for%20the%20modern%20YIMBY%20movement%20was%20California%2C%20where%20sky-high%20home%20prices%20forced%20people%20to%20reconsider%20their%20attitudes%20toward%20development.%3Cp%3ETayfun%20Coskun%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20more%20people%20face%20soaring%20rents%20and%20eye-watering%20home%20prices%2C%20cities%20and%20states%20across%20the%20country%20have%20begun%20to%20get%20serious%20about%20bringing%20down%20the%20cost%20of%20housing.%20And%20that's%20where%20YIMBYs%20have%20stepped%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202018%2C%20Minneapolis%20became%20the%20first%20city%20to%20ban%20single-family%20zoning.%20The%20state%20of%20Oregon%20followed%20soon%20after.%20In%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faustin-real-estate-housing-market-prices-houston-zoning-affordable-2023-8%5C%22%3EAustin%2C%20the%20city%20council%20recently%20passed%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20set%20of%20upzoning%20measures%20that%20include%20reducing%20the%20city's%20minimum%20lot%20size%20%E2%80%94%20which%20would%20allow%20at%20least%20three%20homes%20on%20a%20single%20lot%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20policymakers%20in%20Dallas%20are%20pushing%20for%20a%20similar%20policy.%20Seattle%20homeowners%20built%201%2C000%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fphotos-a-seattle-tiny-home-designed-to-maximize-sunlight-2023-7%23adus-like-this-one-are-popular-in-2022-the-city-of-seattle-issued-1000-adu-permits-to-homeowners-10%5C%22%3EADUs%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20year%2C%20more%20than%20the%20total%20single-family%20homes%20constructed.%20After%20Portland%2C%20Oregon%2C%20passed%20reforms%20that%20allowed%20for%20more%20ADUs%2C%20construction%20of%20the%20units%20increased%20by%2034%25%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Cato%20Institute.%20Some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdenver-makes-it-easier-to-build-backyard-tiny-homes-adu-2023-7%5C%22%3Ecities%20where%20ADUs%20are%3C%2Fa%3E%20growing%20in%20popularity%2C%20like%20Denver%2C%20have%20recently%20eased%20restrictions%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftexas-new-york-pro-housing-legislation-failed-affordability-shortage-2023-5%5C%22%3ENew%20York%20and%20Texas%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20proposed%20far-reaching%20pro-housing%20legislation%20that%20failed%20to%20pass%20their%20state%20legislatures%20this%20year.%20But%20housing%20advocates%20say%20the%20efforts%20in%20both%20states%20shifted%20the%20discourse%20in%20the%20direction%20of%20YIMBYism%20and%20cleared%20the%20path%20for%20more%20narrow%20reforms%20to%20pass.%20But%20similar%20legislation%20passed%20in%20other%20cities%20has%20fallen%20short.%20In%20the%20four%20years%20since%20Minneapolis%20passed%20laws%20that%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.minnpost.com%2Fmetro%2F2019%2F05%2Faccessory-dwelling-units-were-supposed-to-help-ease-the-twin-cities-housing-crunch-hows-that-working-out%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eallow%20ADUs%2C%20%3C%2Fa%3Eonly%20167%20have%20been%20built%2C%20the%20online%20newspaper%20MinnPost%20reported.%20The%20problem%20is%20that%2C%20unlike%20California%20laws%2C%20Minneapolis'%20policy%20%26quot%3Bnever%20got%20into%20the%20how%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Muhammad%20Alameldin%2C%20a%20policy%20associate%20at%20the%20University%20of%20California-Berkeley%20Terner%20Center%20for%20Housing%20Innovation.%20It%20didn't%20consider%20things%20like%20how%20big%20the%20units%20could%20be%2C%20the%20permitting%20fees%2C%20and%20where%20they%20could%20go%20on%20the%20property.%20The%20city%20didn't%20allow%20new%20multiunit%20buildings%20to%20be%20taller%20or%20wider%20than%20the%20single-family%20homes%20they%20replaced%2C%20making%20construction%20less%20financially%20attractive%20to%20developers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EBipartisan%20appeal%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20age%20of%20extreme%20political%20polarization%2C%20housing%20policy%20breaks%20the%20trend.%20There's%20broad%2C%20albeit%20nuanced%2C%20support%20for%20housing%20abundance%20across%20the%20political%20spectrum.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20really%2C%20really%20beneficial%20to%20the%20cause%20of%20housing%20abundance%20that%20it's%20a%20place%20where%20strange%20bedfellows%20can%20sometimes%20come%20together%20to%20make%20reforms%20possible%2C%26quot%3B%20Emily%20Hamilton%2C%20a%20housing%20researcher%20at%20the%20libertarian-leaning%20Mercatus%20Center%20at%20George%20Mason%20University%2C%20told%20Insider.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProgressive%20YIMBYs%20tend%20to%20be%20more%20supportive%20of%20subsidized%20housing%2C%20rent%20stabilization%2C%20and%20other%20government%20measures%20to%20support%20affordable%20housing.%20They%20also%20tend%20to%20be%20more%20environmentally%20minded%20and%20want%20to%20see%20denser%20cities%20limit%20the%20amount%20that%20people%20drive.%20Conservative%20or%20libertarian%20YIMBYs%20tend%20to%20be%20more%20in%20favor%20of%20getting%20the%20government%20out%20of%20the%20housing%20market%20and%20building%20sprawl%20in%20addition%20to%20infill%20housing%20in%20cities.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EWe're%20unwinding%20nearly%20a%20century%20of%20bad%20policy%2C%20of%20policies%20specifically%20designed%20to%20limit%20housing%20supply%20and%20segregate%20our%20cities%20and%20drive%20sprawl%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ppic.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fcrosstabs-all-adults-0723.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERecent%20polling%20in%20California%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20Democrats%20were%20much%20more%20likely%20than%20Republicans%20to%20support%20requiring%20local%20governments%20to%20build%20their%20%26quot%3Bfair%20share%26quot%3B%20of%20affordable%20housing.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20Republicans%20were%20much%20more%20likely%20than%20Democrats%20to%20support%20easing%20current%20land-use%20and%20environmental%20restrictions%20to%20increase%20the%20housing%20supply.%20While%20there%20are%20some%20shades%20of%20disagreement%2C%20the%20primary%20goal%20remains%20the%20same%3A%20more%20housing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFlexibility%20in%20messaging%20is%20one%20of%20the%20real%20strengths%20of%20the%20pro-housing%20movement%2C%26quot%3B%20Jenny%20Schuetz%2C%20an%20expert%20in%20urban%20economics%20and%20housing%20policy%20at%20the%20Brookings%20Institute%2C%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20sign%20of%20just%20how%20flexible%20YIMBY%20ideas%20can%20be%2C%20Montana's%20far-right%20Republican%20governor%2C%20Greg%20Gianforte%2C%20signed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmontana-republicans-anti-california-message-pro-housing-affordability-building-density-2023-4%5C%22%3Ea%20slew%20of%20bipartisan%20pro-housing%20policies%3C%2Fa%3E%20into%20law%20earlier%20this%20year.%20The%20sales%20pitch%3F%20Anti-California%20sentiment.%20The%20broad%20coalition%20of%20organizations%20behind%20the%20policies%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0which%20will%20loosen%20zoning%20laws%20and%20increase%20urban%20density%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0warned%20that%20soaring%20prices%20in%20major%20cities%20like%20Bozeman%20meant%20the%20state%20was%20headed%20toward%20a%20California-style%20housing%20crisis.%20Gray%2C%20of%20California%20YIMBY%2C%20testified%20at%20a%20legislative%20hearing%20on%20behalf%20of%20one%20of%20Montana's%20upzoning%20bills%20and%20used%20his%20home%20state's%20housing%20crisis%20as%20a%20cautionary%20tale%20to%20get%20his%20point%20across.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20testimony%20was%2C%20literally%2C%20if%20you%20want%20to%20avoid%20becoming%20California%2C%20now's%20the%20time%20to%20adopt%20reforms%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20sales%20pitch%20was%20a%20winner%3A%20Bipartisan%20majorities%20in%20the%20state%20legislature%20passed%20seven%20pro-housing%20bills%20and%20the%20governor%20has%20asked%20his%20housing%20task%20force%20to%20identify%20even%20more%20opportunities%20for%20reform.%20Supporters%20call%20it%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mercatus.org%2Fresearch%2Fpolicy-briefs%2Ffour-elements-successful-housing-task-force-lessons-montana-miracle%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BMontana%20Miracle.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20red%20states%20like%20Texas%20and%20Florida%20have%20long%20sold%20themselves%20as%20affordable%20refuges%20from%20unaffordable%20coastal%20blue%20states%20like%20California%20and%20New%20York.%20But%20as%20once-relatively%20affordable%20cities%20like%20Austin%20and%20Miami%20have%20transformed%20into%20some%20of%20the%20most%20expensive%20places%20in%20the%20country%2C%20red%20states%20have%20adopted%20YIMBY%20policies%20to%20retain%20a%20main%20source%20of%20their%20appeal%20for%20newcomers%20and%20longtime%20residents%20alike.%20The%20broad%20political%20appeal%20even%20extends%20to%20the%20federal%20level.%20Republican%20Sen.%20Todd%20Young%20of%20Indiana%20and%20Democratic%20Sen.%20Brian%20Schatz%20of%20Hawaii%20have%20spearheaded%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.young.senate.gov%2Fnewsroom%2Fpress-releases%2Fyoung-colleagues-reintroduce-bill-to-cut-burdensome-regulations-increase-housing-opportunities-for-americans%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EYes%20In%20My%20Backyard%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20would%20boost%20transparency%20and%20urge%20affordable-housing%20construction.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20sea%20change%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20jazzed%20as%20they%20are%20by%20the%20surge%20in%20cross-spectrum%20support%20for%20housing%20abundance%2C%20YIMBY%20activists%20warn%20that%20changing%20laws%20and%20implementing%20reforms%20is%20slow.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20unwinding%20nearly%20a%20century%20of%20bad%20policy%2C%20of%20policies%20specifically%20designed%20to%20limit%20housing%20supply%20and%20segregate%20our%20cities%20and%20drive%20sprawl%2C%26quot%3B%20Gray%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20it%20takes%20time%20to%20unpack%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20YIMBYism%20prevails%20and%20more%20local%20and%20state%20governments%20embrace%20housing%20abundance%2C%20it%20could%20have%20profound%20impacts%20on%20the%20average%20American%20and%20the%20economy%20more%20broadly.%20Denser%20new%20housing%2C%20particularly%20near%20mass%20transit%2C%20could%20help%20fight%20the%20climate%20crisis%20by%20creating%20more%20walkable%2C%20less%20car-dependent%20cities.%20More%20affordable%20housing%20could%20help%20alleviate%20homelessness.%20Families%20and%20young%20people%20could%20move%20to%20opportunity%2C%20rather%20than%20being%20locked%20out%20of%20the%20most%20resource-rich%20neighborhoods.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20movement%2C%20said%20Trauss%2C%20is%20%26quot%3Breally%20still%20at%20the%20beginning.%26quot%3B%20For%20all%20the%20potential%20in%20the%20future%2C%20as%20long%20as%20the%20housing%20crisis%20persists%2C%20YIMBYism%20will%20have%20to%20battle%20against%20long-entrenched%20NIMBYism%20in%20communities%20and%20governments%20across%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20data-mrf-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Feliza-relman%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-uri%3D%5C%22c19804eacd372b9cf134b701ab612126%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%22100%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Feliza-relman%5C%22%20data-analytics-product-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%3EEliza%20Relman%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20policy%20correspondent%20focused%20on%20housing%2C%20transportation%2C%20and%20infrastructure%20on%20Insider's%20economy%20team.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fkelsey-neubauer%5C%22%3EKelsey%20Neubauer%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20real%20estate%20reporter%20for%20Insider%20focused%20on%20housing%20affordability%2C%20where%20people%20are%20moving%2C%20prefab%20%26amp%3B%20modular%20construction%2C%20and%20tiny%20homes.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyimbys-winning-lower-house-prices-rents-build-more-homes-neighborhoods-2023-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694