der.com%2F64f9928e8a7840001961dc3c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221229%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMelissa%20Phillipi%20is%20VP%20of%20organizational%20management%20at%20Vaco.%20%3Cp%3EMelissa%20Phillipi%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ENot%20preparing%20enough%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20preparing%20for%20a%20performance%20review%20is%20like%20cramming%20for%20an%20exam%20the%20night%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnsuccessful%20performance%20reviews%20happen%20when%20there%20was%20little-to-no%20coaching%20along%20the%20way%2C%20there%20was%20limited%20preparation%20ahead%20of%20the%20actual%20performance%20review%2C%20and%20discussion%20around%20goals%20or%20behaviors%20did%20not%20occur%20leading%20up%20to%20the%20performance%20review.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProfessional%20relationships%20are%20no%20different%20from%20personal%20relationships.%20Romantic%20partners%20or%20a%20couple%20of%20friends%20wouldn't%20wait%20all%20year%20to%20celebrate%20wins%20or%20air%20their%20grievances%20in%20one%20mammoth%20conversation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhy%20would%20we%20expect%20a%20performance%20review%20to%20go%20well%20when%20we%20haven't%20put%20in%20the%20time%20and%20effort%20leading%20up%20to%20this%20critical%20conversation%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMake%20sure%20clear%20goals%20are%20set%20that%20align%20with%20organizational%20objectives%2C%20check%20in%20with%20your%20employees%20monthly%20to%20discuss%20progress%20toward%20both%20personal%20and%20professional%20goals%2C%20gather%20feedback%20well%20in%20advance%2C%20and%20%3Cem%3Ethen%20%3C%2Fem%3Eschedule%20the%20performance%20review.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EGiving%20contradictory%20ratings%20and%20commentary%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20performance%20review%20prep%20sessions%20with%20managers%2C%20there%20are%20often%20contradictions%20between%20their%20performance%20ratings%20and%20their%20commentary.%C2%A0They%20rate%20the%20employee%20highly%2C%20but%20the%20comments%20tell%20another%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20commentary%20is%20where%20I%20find%20the%20crucial%20feedback%20a%20manager%20is%20trying%20to%20express%20but%20they%20may%20have%20had%20a%20hard%20time%20saying%20to%20their%20employee's%20face.%20Writing%20forces%20clarity%2C%20and%20this%20is%20very%20evident%20at%20performance%20review%20time.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EContradicting%20ratings%20and%20comments%20send%20mixed%20signals%20diluting%20the%20crucial%20feedback%20%E2%80%93%20feedback%20that%20will%20likely%20help%20them%20and%20even%20potentially%20save%20their%20job.%20In%20these%20scenarios%2C%20employees%20are%20often%20confused%20and%20dismiss%20the%20feedback.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EManagers%20should%20be%20brave%20enough%20to%20give%20an%20appropriate%20rating%20if%20an%20employee%20hasn't%20met%20expectations%20on%20a%20particular%20KPI%20or%20competency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EManipulating%20performance%20review%20ratings%20is%20a%20lose-lose%20practice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EReferencing%20an%20employee's%20past%20'sins'%20that%20have%20been%20resolved%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20one%20still%20shocks%20me.%20While%20most%20managers%20are%20afraid%20to%20give%20anything%20less%20than%20positive%20feedback%2C%20some%20people%20get%20strangely%20brave%20behind%20a%20computer%20screen%20%E2%80%93%20and%20tend%20to%20write%20things%20they%20would%20never%20say%20to%20someone's%20face.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20they%20end%20up%20referencing%20old%20%26quot%3Bsins%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%93%20like%20events%2C%20failures%2C%20or%20misjudgments%20the%20employee%20made%20throughout%20the%20year%20%E2%80%93%20that%20have%20already%20been%20addressed%20and%20the%20behavior%20has%20been%20corrected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20this%20is%20a%20common%20mistake%2C%20it's%20also%20incredibly%20destructive.%20Not%20only%20are%20employees%20left%20feeling%20demoralized%2C%20but%20they%20are%20also%20often%20angry%2C%20hurt%2C%20and%20discouraged%20%E2%80%93%20because%20what%20does%20it%20matter%20if%20you've%20improved%20if%20your%20past%20will%20always%20be%20there%20to%20haunt%20you%20or%20be%20thrown%20in%20your%20face%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20advise%20managers%20to%20always%20be%20forward%20thinking%3A%20focus%20on%20problems%20that%20have%20yet%20to%20be%20solved%20and%20the%20development%20of%20the%20employee.%20Performance%20reviews%20should%20center%20around%20growth%20as%20well%20as%20providing%20constructive%20feedback.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETaking%20calls%20or%20answering%20emails%20during%20a%20review%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENothing%20says%20%26quot%3Byou're%20not%20very%20important%20to%20me%26quot%3B%20quite%20like%20answering%20a%20call%20or%20checking%20a%20text%20or%20email%20during%20a%20performance%20review%20conversation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20always%20tell%20managers%20to%20put%20themselves%20in%20the%20shoes%20of%20their%20reports.%20Often%20reviews%20are%20stressful%20and%20anxiety-inducing%20for%20employees.%20It's%20unempathetic%20to%20be%20distracted%20by%20an%20email%20or%20someone%20popping%20into%20a%20private%20meeting.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPut%20the%20phone%20away%2C%20turn%20off%20Teams%20or%20Slack%2C%20and%20ensure%20your%20colleagues%20know%20not%20to%20interrupt%20unless%20it's%20a%20true%20emergency%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0maybe%20even%20go%20for%20a%20walk%20or%20take%20the%20performance%20review%20outside.%20This%20is%20a%20priority%2C%20so%20make%20it%20evident.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ELeaving%20no%20time%20for%20future%20development%20discussions%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0A%20professed%20talker%20and%20caffeinated%20extrovert%2C%20I%20understand%20the%20challenge%20of%20keeping%20the%20conversation%20focused%20enough%20to%20stay%20on%20schedule.%20But%20it's%20important%20to%20always%20leave%20time%20at%20the%20end%20of%20a%20review%20to%20discuss%20the%20future%20progression%20of%20an%20employee.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEffective%20managers%20are%20also%20good%20coaches.%20Always%20allow%20time%20to%20ask%20provoking%20questions%20that%20will%20encourage%20employees%20to%20think%20about%20their%20future%20at%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrepared%20managers%20should%20have%20enough%20material%20to%20present%20an%20individual%20development%20plan%20since%20all%20past%20performance%20and%20displays%20of%20behavior%20have%20been%20discussed%20and%20documented%20in%20regular%20one-on-ones%20and%20feedback%20sessions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20simple%20trick%20to%20help%20you%20remember%20to%20do%20this%20is%20to%20write%20a%20question%20or%20two%20on%20your%20employee's%20self-assessment%2C%20such%20as%2C%20%26quot%3BDid%20you%20achieve%20your%20personal%20and%20professional%20goals%20this%20year%3F%20If%20not%2C%20why%3F%20What%20would%20you%20like%20to%20achieve%20this%20year%3F%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EManagers%20should%20gather%20this%20employee%20feedback%20before%20the%20review%20to%20plan%20further%20improvements%20and%20objectives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ETry%20and%20improve%20one%20aspect%20of%20the%20review%20process%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20above%20is%20not%20an%20exhaustive%20list%20of%20mistakes%20to%20avoid%2C%20here's%20my%20advice%20for%20managers%3A%20It's%20better%20to%20do%20something%20about%20one%20thing%20instead%20of%20nothing%20about%20everything.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProductive%20performance%20reviews%20are%20possible%20if%20managers%20take%20small%20steps%20like%20these%20throughout%20the%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmistakes-managers-make-during-performance-reviews-2023-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694078690000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f85d3b04e14000196ca7b6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmistakes-managers-make-