If%20this%20recession%20hasn't%20happened%20by%20the%20first%20quarter%20of%20next%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DQyrgmBNcfSc%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecently%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20WTFinance%20podcast%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20will%20wipe%20the%20egg%20off%20my%20face%2C%20and%20I'll%20write%20a%20report%20saying%2C%20'I%20was%20wrong%2C%20the%20business%20cycle%20has%20been%20repealed%20after%20all.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Federal%20Reserve%20has%20hiked%20interest%20rates%20from%20nearly%20zero%20to%20north%20of%205%25%20since%20last%20spring%20in%20an%20effort%20to%20curb%20historic%20inflation.%20Short-term%20Treasuries%20are%20also%20paying%20larger%20yields%20than%20long-term%20government%20bonds%2C%20signaling%20Wall%20Street%20expects%20an%20economic%20downturn%20to%20spur%20the%20Fed%20to%20cut%20rates%20in%20the%20coming%20years.%20The%20economy%20has%20never%20gone%20through%20a%20Fed%20tightening%20cycle%20where%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fbonds%2Frecession-stock-market-crash-inverted-yield-curve-federal-reserve-powell-2023-6%5C%22%3Eyield%20curve%20was%20inverted%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20not%20suffered%20a%20recession%2C%20Rosenberg%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Rosenberg%20Research%20president%20described%20the%20American%20consumer%20as%20the%20%26quot%3BEnergizer%20bunny%2C%26quot%3B%20because%20households%20have%20kept%20spending%20relentlessly%20for%20the%20past%20couple%20of%20years.%20However%2C%20he%20warned%20their%20stimulus-juiced%20savings%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fbond-king-bill-gross-consumer-spending-outlook-economy-fe-government-2023-7%5C%22%3Eclose%20to%20running%20out%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20student-debt%20repayments%20resumed%20this%20month%2C%20and%20there%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fn