o%20paved%20the%20way%20for%20a%20series%20of%20challenges%20against%20other%20mosques%2C%20including%20the%20one%20in%20Gyanvapi.%20This%20article%20delves%20into%20these%20complex%20layers%2C%20dissecting%20the%20impact%20of%20court%20decisions%20on%20religious%20structures%20and%20the%20broader%20implications%20for%20a%20nation%20striving%20to%20achieve%20social%20harmony%20and%20sustainable%20growth.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20Ayodhya%20judgment%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20Ayodhya%20judgment%20was%20not%20a%20mere%20property%20dispute%20as%20embedded%20in%20it%20was%20an%20act%20of%20religious%20and%20political%20violence%3A%20the%20destruction%20of%20the%20Babri%20Masjid.%20By%20holding%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20Hindus%2C%20the%20court%20ignored%20the%20basic%20principles%20of%20restitution%20that%20parties%20must%20be%20restored%20to%20their%20original%20positions%2C%20where%20possible.%20The%20court%20could%20have%20ordered%20a%20status%20quo%20that%20prevailed%20before%20the%20demolition%20and%20then%20adjudicated%20the%20dispute%2C%20but%20it%20failed%20to%20do%20so.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20(in)action%20of%20the%20court%20fuelled%20the%20%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Findia%2Fstory%2Ftemples-destroyed-build-masjids-reclaimed-legally-karnataka-bjp-mla-eshwarappa-1954842-2022-05-27%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Etemple%20reclamation%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%20movement%20and%20its%20consequences%20can%20now%20be%20seen.%20The%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Findia-news%2F1st-hurdle-to-reclaiming-site-crossed-says-vhp-on-gyanvapi-mosque-verdict-101663058731081.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Efirst%20stage%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%20temple%20reclamation%20has%20become%20filing%20cases%20before%20the%20courts.%20It%20was%20expected%20that%20the%20Ayodhya%20judgment%20would%20settle%20the%20law%2C%20and%20no%20new%20claims%20or%20disputes%20would%20arise%20in%20the%20future.%20However%2C%20the%20Vishwa%20Hindu%20Parishad%20(VHP)%20has%20never%20backed%20down%20on%20its%20demand%20for%20the%20construction%20of%20Hindu%20temples%20in%20Varanasi%2C%20Mathura%20and%20several%20others.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20Arundhati%20Roy%20writes%20in%20her%20book%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAZADI%3A%20Freedom.%20Fascism.%20Fiction%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98%E2%80%98The%20VHP%20has%20refused%20to%20back%20down%20on%20its%20past%20statements%20that%20it%20will%20turn%20its%20attention%20to%20other%20mosques.%20Theirs%20can%20be%20an%20endless%20campaign-%20after%20all%2C%20everybody%20came%20from%20somewhere%2C%20and%20everything%20is%20built%20over%20something.%E2%80%99%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F07141300%2FKashi-gyanvapi_1-1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221064%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F07141300%2FKashi-gyanvapi_1-1.jpg%201064w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F07141300%2FKashi-gyanvapi_1-1-300x203.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F07141300%2FKashi-gyanvapi_1-1-1024x694.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-666974%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22721%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EGyanvapi%20mosque.%20Photo%3A%20Oasis.54515%2FWikimedia%20commons%20CC%20BY-SA%204.0%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20Gyanvapi%20row%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20is%20already%20hearing%20upon%20the%20constitutionality%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiacode.nic.in%2Fbitstream%2F123456789%2F1922%2F1%2Fa1991-42.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Places%20of%20Worship%20%5BSpecial%20Provisions%5D%20Act%2C%201991%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20passed%20during%20the%20heat%20of%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20dispute%20in%201991.%20The%20law%20bans%20the%20conversion%20of%20any%20place%20of%20worship%20to%20preserve%20its%20character%20as%20it%20was%20during%20the%20time%20of%20independence%20of%20India.%20Despite%20being%20challenged%20before%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20the%20Act%20still%20exists%20and%20is%20in%20force.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYet%2C%20a%20petition%20was%20filed%20by%20five%20Hindu%20women%20in%20April%2C%202022%20before%20a%20Varanasi%20Court%20claiming%20their%20right%20to%20worship%20since%20they%20believed%20there%20exists%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3Eshivling%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cspan%3Eunder%20the%20Gyanvapi%20Mosque%2C%20which%20was%20constructed%20by%20Aurangzeb%20after%20destroying%20a%20temple.%20An%20archaeological%20survey%20of%20the%20mosque%20was%20ordered%20in%20May%2C%202022%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fgyanvapi-case-court-orders-sealing-of-spot-where-shivling-reportedly-found%2Farticle65419231.ece%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eled%20to%20an%20object%20resembling%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eshivling%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eallegedly%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20being%20found%20inside%20the%20mosque%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ewazukhana%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E(ablution%20pond)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EConsequently%2C%20an%20order%20was%20passed%20that%20namaz%20would%20not%20be%20allowed%20in%20the%20mosque%3B%20however%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20ordered%20to%20restore%20the%20offering%20of%20namaz%20and%20preservation%20of%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ew%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eazukhana%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fsupreme-court-declines-to-stay-hc-order-permitting-asi-survey-of-gyanvapi-mosque-8876521%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Edirecting%20the%20Varanasi%20district%20judge%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20hear%20the%20matter.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fgyanvapi-litmus-test-system-failed%5C%22%3EGyanvapi%20Is%20a%20Litmus%20Test%20for%20the%20Sanctity%20of%20the%20Places%20of%20Worship%20Act.%20Our%20System%20Failed%20It.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20petition%20of%20those%20five%20women%20was%20challenged%20by%20the%20Masjid%20Intazamia%20on%20the%20grounds%20of%20its%20maintainability%20itself%20that%20The%20Places%20of%20Worship%20Act%2C%201991%20is%20in%20force%2C%20and%20such%20a%20petition%20cannot%20be%20entertained%20that%20seeks%20to%20convert%20any%20religious%20place%20of%20worship%20as%20barred%20by%20Section%203%20of%20the%20Act.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20district%20judge%20rejected%20this%20argument%20as%20he%20ruled%20that%20the%20law%20prevents%20the%20conversion%20of%20the%20place%20of%20worship%2C%20whereas%2C%20in%20this%20petition%2C%20the%20question%20is%20about%20the%20%E2%80%98determination%20and%20ascertainment%20of%20the%20character%20of%20the%20place%20of%20worship%E2%80%99%2C%20which%20is%20not%20barred%20by%20the%20Act.%20This%20interpretation%20that%20the%20district%20judge%20has%20provided%20for%20Section%203%20is%20enough%20to%20open%20a%20floodgate%20of%20litigation%20before%20the%20courts.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFurthermore%2C%20the%20State%20of%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20had%20enacted%20a%20legislation%2C%20namely%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprsindia.org%2Ffiles%2Fbills_acts%2Facts_states%2Futtar-pradesh%2F1983%2F1983UP29.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20Sri%20Kashi%20Vishwanath%20Temple%20Act%2C%201983%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20which%20defines%20a%20temple%20under%20section%204%5B9%5D%20which%20pertains%20to%20the%20temple%20of%20Adi%20Vishweshwar%2C%20popularly%20known%20as%20Sri%20Kashi%20Vishwanath%20temple%2C%20situated%20in%20Varanasi.%20Hence%20the%20Gyanvapi%20Mosque%20is%20to%20be%20considered%20a%20temple%20as%20per%20this%20law.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20the%20apex%20court%20will%20determine%20the%20constitutionality%20of%20the%201991%20Act%2C%20it%20is%20still%20valid%20and%20needs%20to%20be%20followed%20in%20the%20meantime.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cb%3ESimilar%20trajectory%20in%20the%20Mathura%20case%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Shahi%20Idgah%20Mosque%20in%20Mathura%20is%20the%20subject%20of%20more%20than%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fallahabad%2Fsolve-krishna-janmabhoomi-cases-in-4-months-allahabad-hc-to-mathura-court%2Farticleshow%2F91531345.cms%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Edozen%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3Ecases.%20The%20first%20of%20these%20cases%20was%20filed%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20Ayodhya%20judgment.%20Based%20on%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20order%20in%20the%20Gyanvapi%20case%2C%20the%20petitioners%20requested%20a%20similar%20video%20survey%20of%20the%20mosque%20and%20the%20local%20court%20in%20Mathura%20agreed%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.timesnownews.com%2Findia%2Fkrishna-janmabhoomi-row-mathura-court-agrees-to-hear-plea-for-videography-of-shahi-idgah-mosque-article-91615190%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehear%20the%20plea%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20seen%20from%20the%20aforementioned%20cases%2C%20the%20courts%20seem%20to%20be%20developing%20a%20jurisprudence%20on%20religious%20conversions%20that%20is%20not%20grounded%20in%20the%20laws.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cb%3EWhy%20are%20the%20courts%20acting%20in%20this%20manner%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20possible%20reason%20why%20courts%20seem%20to%20be%20sympathetic%20to%20the%20Hindu%20cause%20may%20be%20that%20they%20want%20to%20respect%20the%20faith%20of%20the%20majority.%20They%20may%20also%20hold%20the%20opinion%20that%20even%20if%20they%20rule%20according%20to%20the%20law%2C%20people%20would%20be%20forced%20to%20bow%20down%20to%20societal%20pressures%20%E2%80%93%20like%20in%20the%20Sabarimala%20case%20where%2C%20ultimately%2C%20prevailing%20pressures%20led%20to%20only%20two%20women%20entering%20the%20temple%2C%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20night%2C%20with%20government%20help%20and%20leading%20to%20multiple%20attacks%20afterwards.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20while%20a%20frenzied%20mob%20can%20demolish%20the%20mosque%20on%20the%20spur%20of%20the%20moment%2C%20it%20would%20not%20have%20been%20possible%20to%20construct%20the%20temple%20without%20the%20help%20of%20the%20court%20and%20the%20state.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cb%3EBabri%20Masjid%20demolition%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Babri%20Masjid%20demolition%20was%20soon%20followed%20by%2C%20what%20were%20then%20called%2C%20serial%20bomb%20blasts%20in%20Mumbai%20in%20early%201993%20and%20began%20being%20called%20terrorist%20attacks%20after%20the%202001%20attack%20on%20the%20twin%20towers%20in%20New%20York.%20India%20witnessed%20many%20terrorist%20attacks%20after%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20demolition%20including%20the%20one%20in%202008%20in%20Mumbai.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERadicalisation%20of%20Islam%20and%20Muslim%20youth%20was%20an%20outcome%20of%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20demolition%20and%20more%20such%20injustices%20are%20likely%20to%20elicit%20more%20reactions%20from%20the%20Muslim%20community.%20This%20is%20something%20that%20the%20judiciary%20must%20keep%20in%20mind%20when%20deciding%20the%20fate%20of%20Islamic%20historical%20religious%20structures.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20case%20stated%20that%20the%20principle%20of%20non-retrogression%20should%20be%20followed%20as%20the%20court%20will%20not%20undo%20the%20historical%20injustices%20by%20the%20previous%20rulers%20of%20the%20country%20or%20its%20parts%20thereof.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98%E2%80%98This%20Court%20cannot%20entertain%20claims%20that%20stem%20from%20the%20actions%20of%20the%20Mughal%20rulers%20against%20Hindu%20places%20of%20worship%20in%20a%20court%20of%20law%20today.%20For%20any%20person%20who%20seeks%20solace%20or%20recourse%20against%20the%20actions%20of%20any%20number%20of%20ancient%20rulers%2C%20the%20law%20is%20not%20the%20answer.%20Our%20history%20is%20replete%20with%20actions%20that%20have%20been%20judged%20to%20be%20morally%20incorrect%20and%20even%20today%20are%20liable%20to%20trigger%20vociferous%20ideological%20debate%2C%E2%80%99%E2%80%99%20the%20court%20had%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0It%20is%20unfortunate%20that%20this%20part%20of%20the%20judgment%20has%20been%20ignored%20by%20the%20lower%20courts%20which%20are%20encouraging%20litigations%20such%20as%20Gyanvapi%20and%20Mathura%20through%20favourable%20orders%20to%20the%20petitioners%20and%20thereby%20encouraging%20them%20to%20file%20more%20such%20cases%20that%20browbeat%20religious%20interests%20of%20the%20minority%20communities.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20courts%20are%20supposed%20to%20be%20the%20custodians%20of%20the%20constitution.%20If%20they%20start%20giving%20in%20to%20the%20majority%20sentiment%2C%20the%20distinction%20between%20the%20judiciary%20and%20legislature%20will%20be%20lost.%20The%20legislature%20can%20still%20overrule%20the%20court%20like%20in%20the%20case%20of%20Shah%20Bano%20but%20the%20judiciary%20has%20to%20stand%20its%20ground.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EVishnu%20Bandarupalli%20and%20Ayush%20Bajpai%20are%20students%20of%20law%20at%20NALSAR%2C%20Hyderabad%20and%20Sandeep%20Pandey%20is%20General%20Secretary%2C%20Socialist%20Party%20(India).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694071827000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F06%2F03203736%2FScreenshot-2022-06-03-at-8.37.31-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fwhat-can-the-courts-do-when-religion-is-politicised%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20aftermath%20of%20the%20Ayodhya%20judgment%20not%20only%20redefined%20the%20boundaries%20between%20history%2C%20religion%2C%20and%20legality%20but%20also%20paved%20the%20way%20for%20a%20series%20of%20challenges%20against%20other%20mosques.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fwhat-can-the-courts-do-when-religion-is-politicised%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Mexico%20decriminalises%20abortion%20nationwide%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694071500000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F09%2F768x432%2Fskynews-mexico-abortion_6277066.jpg%3F20230907090651%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fmexico-decriminalises-abortion-nationwide-12956564%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Mexico's%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20decriminalised%20abortion%20nationwide.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fmexico-decriminalises-abortion-nationwide-12956564%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fmexico-decriminalises-abortion-nationwide-12956564%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fmexico-decriminalises-abortion-nationwide-12956564%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Diaspora%20-%20A%20Driving%20Force%20Behind%20India's%20G20%20Success%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAs%20part%20of%20India's%20G20%20presidency%2C%20which%20culminates%20in%20a%20mega%20summit%20of%20world%20leaders%20this%20weekend%2C%20Indiaspora's%20G20%20forum%20in%20August%20featured%20300%20trailblazers%20of%20the%20Indian%20diaspora%20from%2026%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indiaspora%20forum%2C%20looking%20to%20emerge%20as%20the%20%26quot%3BDavos%20for%20the%20Global%20Indian%26quot%3B%2C%20explored%20how%20the%20diaspora%20can%20contribute%20to%20the%20success%20of%20%26quot%3BIndia%40100%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20year%202047.%20The%20participants%20included%20ambassadors%2C%20cabinet%20secretaries%2C%20investors%2C%20entrepreneurs%2C%20corporate%20titans%2C%20philanthropists%2C%20academics%2C%20artists%2C%20healthcare%20practitioners%2C%20next%20generation%20torchbearers%2C%20AI%20savants%20and%20environmental%20experts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndiaspora%2C%20a%20non-profit%20founded%20in%20the%20US%20in%202012%2C%20works%20actively%20in%20eight%20countries%20and%20seeks%20to%20establish%20strong%20relationships%20in%20at%20least%2020%20more.%20We%20count%20among%20us%20political%20and%20public%20policy%20leaders%2C%20Fortune%20500%20CEOs%2C%20academicians%2C%20artists%2C%20legal%20luminaries%2C%20doctors%2C%20scientists%2C%20investors%2C%20environmentalists%20and%2C%20of%20course%2C%20entrepreneurs.%20People%20of%20Indian%20origin%20are%20even%20starting%20to%20make%20a%20headway%20in%20the%20American%20sporting%20arena%2C%20which%20was%20so%20far%20a%20scarcely%20considered%20vocation%20for%20most%20of%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20casual%20observers%20have%20noticed%20that%20America%20is%20paying%20close%20attention%20to%20India%2C%20and%20is%20proactively%20seeking%20to%20bolster%20bilateral%20relations.%20Witness%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi's%20recent%20watershed%20state%20visit%2C%20and%20the%20substantive%2C%20in-depth%20dialogues%20that%20took%20place%20during%20his%20stay.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20benefits%20from%20the%20diaspora's%20close%20relationship%20to%20the%20homeland.%20A%20case%20in%20point%20-%20diaspora%20remittances%20to%20India%20topped%20US%20%24100%20billion%20in%202022.%20This%20amount%20is%2027%20percent%20higher%20than%20foreign%20direct%20investment.%20Not%20surprisingly%2C%20almost%20a%20quarter%20of%20these%20remittances%20came%20from%20the%20US%20alone.%20Cross-border%20financial%20flows%20are%20not%20the%20only%20item%20of%20note.%20According%20to%20a%20recent%20estimate%2C%20while%20people%20of%20Indian%20origin%20comprise%20slightly%20more%20than%20one%20percent%20of%20the%20American%20population%2C%20they%20account%20for%206%20percent%20of%20the%20USA's%20tax%20coffers.%20This%2C%20among%20other%20factors%2C%20enables%20the%20Indian%20diaspora%20to%20have%20a%20powerful%20voice%20on%20issues%20of%20bilateral%20importance%20in%20the%20US-India%20corridor.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20recent%20impetus%20for%20education-sector%20collaboration%20between%20the%20two%20countries%20has%20received%20a%20big%20boost%20from%20the%20Indian%20diaspora%20in%20the%20US.%20This%20topic%20was%20explored%20in%20a%20panel%20discussion%20at%20the%20Indiaspora%20G20%20Forum.%20On%20immigration%20and%20visas%2C%20a%20vexed%20issue%20for%20millions%2C%20diaspora%20organisations%20in%20the%20US%20(including%20Indiaspora)%2C%20helped%20effect%20changes%20in%20processes%20and%20rules%2C%20and%20are%20working%20further%20to%20advocate%20for%20helpful%20legislation.%20During%20the%20early%20stages%20of%20COVID%2C%20India%20needed%20raw%20materials%20to%20begin%20manufacturing%20vaccines.%20The%20Indian%20diaspora%20facilitated%20the%20transfer%20of%20material%2C%20technology%20and%20knowhow%20from%20the%20US%20to%20India%2C%20with%20the%20result%20that%20India%20became%20a%20sought-after%20and%20reliable%20global%20vaccine%20supplier.%20These%20are%20concrete%2C%20constructive%20and%20beneficial%20roles%20that%20the%20diaspora%20has%20played%20just%20in%20the%20recent%20past.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20worth%20reiterating%20that%20the%20diaspora%20was%20key%20in%20bringing%20America%20and%20India%20together%20for%20the%20breakthrough%20civil%20nuclear%20agreement%20nearly%20two%20decades%20ago.%20Previous%20G20%20presidencies%20were%20centred%20on%20specific%20subject%20areas%20such%20as%20empowering%20women%2C%20fighting%20corruption%2C%20strengthening%20financial%20governance%2C%20fairness%20of%20the%20global%20tax%20system%2C%20trade%20and%20investment%2C%20and%20climate%20action.%20India%20has%20chosen%20a%20more%20overarching%20theme%2C%20with%20defined%20areas%20of%20focus%20beneath%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20absence%20of%20two%20significant%20leaders%20in%20the%20Indian%20capital%20does%20not%20diminish%20the%20aspirational%20value%20of%20India's%20G20%20slogan%2C%20%26quot%3BVasudhaiva%20Kutumbakam%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3BOne%20Earth%20-%20One%20Family%20-%20One%20Future%26quot%3B%2C%20which%20positions%20it%20as%20a%20unifier%20among%20nations.%20As%20India%20ascends%20to%20become%20a%20global%20power%2C%20the%20diaspora%20would%20do%20well%20to%20take%20to%20heart%20the%20spirit%20of%20India's%20G20%20presidency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20India's%20diaspora%20continues%20to%20rise%20to%20positions%20of%20prominence%20in%20a%20variety%20of%20occupations%20across%20the%20globe%2C%20India%20benefits%20by%20harnessing%20their%20skills%2C%20networks%2C%20stature%20and%20emotional%20ties%20to%20their%20country%20of%20origin.%20This%20symbiosis%20augurs%20well%20for%20India's%20progress%20towards%20100%20years%20of%20independence%20and%20beyond.%20The%20Leaders'%20Summit%20is%20viewed%20as%20a%20culmination%20of%20India's%20G20%20presidency.%20From%20the%20diaspora%20dimension%2C%20it%20is%20a%20clarion%20call%20for%20a%20shared%20and%20brighter%20future%2C%20full%20of%20possibilities%20as%20a%20force%20for%20good.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E(MR%20Rangaswami%20is%20Indiaspora's%20Founder%20and%20Chairman%20in%20San%20Francisco%20and%20Sanjeev%20Joshipura%20is%20Indiaspora's%20Executive%20Director%20in%20Washington%2C%20D.C)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20authors.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694070780000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2Fs5ivvk0g_delhi-g20-summit-photo-feature_625x300_22_August_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fopinion-diaspora-a-driving-force-behind-indias-g20-success-4367407%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20part%20of%20India's%20G20%20presidency%2C%20which%20culminates%20in%20a%20mega%20summit%20of%20world%20leaders%20this%20weekend%2C%20Indiaspora's%20G20%20forum%20in%20August%20featured%20300%20trailblazers%20of%20the%20Indian%20diaspora%20from%2026%20countries.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fopinion-diaspora-a-driving-force-behind-indias-g20-success-4367407%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fopinion-diaspora-a-driving-force-behind-indias-g20-success-4367407%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fopinion-diaspora-a-driving-force-behind-indias-g20-success-4367407%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Venice%20Offers%20New%20Senses%20and%20Directions%20in%20XR%3A%26nbsp%3B%E2%80%98All%20Projects%20Involve%20the%20Human%20Body%2C%20We%E2%80%99re%20Not%20Just%20Sitting%E2%80%99%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694070644000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fimage0-11.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22ori