ic%20violence%20between%20Manipur%E2%80%99s%20largest%20community%2C%20the%20Meiteis%2C%20and%20its%20%5Bthird%5D-largest%20one%2C%20the%20Kukis%2C%20has%20killed%20hundreds%20of%20people%20and%20rendered%2060%2C000%20people%20homeless.%20Mobs%20have%20set%20fire%20to%20over%20350%20churches%20and%20vandalised%20over%20a%20dozen%20temples.%20They%20have%20burned%20more%20than%20200%20villages%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20report%20in%20the%20influential%20American%20international%20relations%20magazine%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.foreignaffairs.com%2Findia%2Fwhy-modi-cant-make-india-great-power%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EForeign%20Affairs%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20piece%20contrasts%20India%E2%80%99s%20aims%20to%20become%20a%20model%20for%20the%20world%2C%20with%20its%20reality%2C%20%E2%80%9Cto%20be%20stable%20enough%20to%20project%20substantial%20authority%2C%20India%20needs%20to%20keep%20peace%20and%20harmony%20among%20its%20diverse%20population%20%E2%80%93%20something%20it%20can%20accomplish%20only%20by%20becoming%20an%20inclusive%2C%20plural%2C%20secular%2C%20and%20liberal%20democracy.%20Otherwise%2C%20it%20risks%20turning%20into%20a%20Hindu%20version%20of%20South%20Asia%E2%80%99s%20other%20countries%2C%20such%20as%20Myanmar%20and%20Pakistan%2C%20where%20ethnic%20dominance%20has%20resulted%20in%20tumult%2C%20violence%2C%20and%20deprivation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20highlights%20how%20diverting%20troops%20to%20Manipur%20has%20reduced%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20capacity%20to%20protect%20its%20borders%20from%20an%20increasingly%20aggressive%20China.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20internal%20conflict%20has%20made%20it%20difficult%20for%20India%20to%20become%20an%20influential%20player%20in%20South%20Asia%20by%20preventing%20it%20from%20%E2%80%9Ccarrying%20out%20regional%20infrastructure%20projects%20and%20by%20saddling%20neighbouring%20states%20with%20refugees.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EModi%E2%80%99s%20inability%20to%20adequately%20address%20the%20ethnic%20violence%20or%20ask%20his%20chief%20minister%20to%20mitigate%20the%20situation%20has%20also%20opened%20up%20possibilities%20for%20other%20rebel%20groups%20in%20India%20to%20launch%20their%20own%20campaigns%2C%20further%20undermining%20New%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20primacy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20little%20reason%20to%20think%20that%20tensions%20will%20ease%20under%20Modi%2C%20and%20plenty%20of%20reason%20to%20think%20they%20will%20get%20worse%2C%E2%80%9D%20journalist%20and%20lecturer%20at%20Yale%2C%20Sushant%20Singh%20has%20written%2C%20adding%20that%20he%20feared%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20country%20could%20eventually%20confront%20%E2%80%A6%20a%20million%20mutinies%2C%E2%80%9D%20threatening%20India%E2%80%99s%20own%20being.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E%E2%80%9CIndia%20is%20tearing%20itself%20apart%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEven%20if%20one%20looks%20at%20the%20strides%20India%20has%20made%20under%20Modi%2C%20the%20%E2%80%9Cleader%E2%80%99s%20achievements%20are%20overshadowed%20by%20growing%20authoritarianism%2C%20fuelled%20by%20personal%20and%20ideological%20resentments%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20scholar%2C%20Devesh%20Kapur%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2Fdfda7308-475c-45a3-8abb-ef34087a8f57%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EFinancial%20Times%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20said.%20The%20country%20should%20apply%20its%20expansive%20theme%20for%20the%20event%20%E2%80%94%20%E2%80%98One%20World%2C%20One%20Family%2C%20One%20Future%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%94%20to%20itself%2C%20was%20his%20observation.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CFrom%20a%20railway%20police%20official%20killing%20Muslim%20train%20passengers%20to%20a%20school%20principal%20encouraging%20Hindu%20students%20to%20slap%20a%20Muslim%20student%2C%20bigotry%20is%20becoming%20entrenched.%20Treating%20people%20as%20second-class%20citizens%20erodes%20their%20dignity%20and%20contributions%20to%20society%2C%20while%20nurturing%20resentments%20that%20are%20bound%20to%20have%20pernicious%20consequences%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20added.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20G20%20presidency%20is%20planked%20by%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2Fdfda7308-475c-45a3-8abb-ef34087a8f57%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Emuzzled%20media%20and%20attacks%20on%20independent%20think-tanks%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3Eand%20academics%20on%20one%20side%2C%20and%20%E2%80%9Cundermining%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20delicate%20federal%20balance%20in%20an%20ethnically%20complex%20multinational%20state%E2%80%9D%20on%20the%20other.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20weaponisation%20of%20the%20coercive%20arms%20of%20the%20state%20is%20being%20driven%20by%20the%20man%20commonly%20referred%20to%20as%20India%E2%80%99s%20second%20most%20powerful%20leader%20%E2%80%93%20Amit%20Shah%2C%20whose%20writ%20runs%20over%20large%20parts%20of%20the%20central%20government.%20But%20his%20own%20ministry%20has%20been%20failing%20in%20its%20core%20duties.%20For%20the%20first%20time%20since%201881%20(barring%20a%20gap%20during%20the%20second%20world%20war)%2C%20the%20decennial%20Indian%20census%20of%202021%20has%20not%20been%20conducted%2C%20leaving%20the%20state%20without%20updated%20data%20to%20address%20governance%20challenges%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20piece%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EFT%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20pointed%20out.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ENo%20joint%20statements%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EInternal%20conflicts%20notwithstanding%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20G20%20presidency%20has%20also%20been%20marked%20by%20a%20glaring%20lack%20of%20joint%20statements%20issued%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20many%20meetings%20held%2