he%20case%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fassam-accord-section-6a-citizenship-supreme-court%5C%22%3Eargue%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20separate%20cut%20off%20date%20for%20Assam%20%E2%80%93%20the%20cut%20off%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20India%20is%20July%2019%2C%201949%20%E2%80%93%20is%20%E2%80%9Cunconstitutional%E2%80%9D%20and%20urged%20that%201951%20be%20considered%20the%20base%20year%20for%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20listed%20the%20case%20for%20hearing%20in%20front%20of%20constitution%20benches%20before%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fnew-constitution-bench-in-supreme-court-to-hear-issues-related-to-assam-nrc-reservations-in-legislative-assemblies-immunity-for-mpsmlas-in-bribery-cases-237088%5C%22%3Ebut%20these%20have%20had%20to%20be%20reconstituted%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20its%20judges%20retired%2C%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAshok%20Kumar%20Jain%20vs.%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20second%20case%2C%20involves%20a%20challenge%20to%20the%20extension%20of%20reservations%20in%20Union%20and%20state%20legislatures%20to%20members%20of%20Scheduled%20Castes%20and%20Scheduled%20Tribes%20(and%20originally%20to%20Anglo-Indians%20as%20well).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPetitioners%20in%20this%20case%20contend%20that%20the%20extensions%20violated%20the%20right%20to%20equality%20of%20those%20not%20belonging%20to%20the%20above%20communities%2C%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20third%20case%20listed%20before%20this%20constitution%20bench%2C%20%3Cem%3ESita%20Soren%20vs.%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20apex%20court%20has%20to%20decide%20whether%20Article%20194(2)%20of%20the%20constitution%20grants%20immunity%20to%20state-level%20legislators%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsc-legislator-immunity-amicus-appointed%5C%22%3Eaccepting%20bribes%20to%20make%20speeches%20or%20votes%20in%20the%20legislature%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESita%20Soren%2C%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Jharkhand%20legislative%20assembly%2C%20was%20accused%20by%20the%20Central%20Bureau%20of%20Investigation%20of%20accepting%20a%20bribe%20to%20vote%20for%20a%20candidate%20in%20the%202012%20Rajya%20Sabha%20elections.%20She%20claimed%20immunity%20from%20prosecution%20under%20Article%20194(2)%20but%20the%20Jharkhand%20high%20court%20rejected%20her%20plea%2C%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20then%20approached%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20for%20relief.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Findia-news%2Fcan-parliamentary-privilege-protect-tainted-leaders-supreme-court-to-hear%2Fstory-Jb5DkzyPQNQHyQqTJtJOhM.html%5C%22%3EWhile%20deliberating%20her%20case%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20court%20referenced%20a%201998%20ruling%20by%20one%20of%20its%20constitution%20benches%20(%3Cem%3EP.V.%20Narasimha%20Rao%20vs.%20State%3C%2Fem%3E)%2C%20which%20said%20that%20parliamentarians%20had%20immunity%20against%20criminal%20prosecution%20for%20their%20speeches%20and%20votes%20inside%20the%20House.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%C2%A0%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20thought%20it%20fit%20to%20refer%20Soren%E2%80%99s%20matter%20before%20a%20constitution%20bench%20so%20that%20it%20could%20reconsider%20its%20judgement%20in%C2%A0%3Cem%3EP.V.%20Narasimha%20Rao%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694022204000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F10%2F30154000%2FScreen-Shot-2019-10-30-at-3.39.36-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-creates-new-constitution-bench-to-hear-three-cases%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20new%20bench%20comprises%20five%20judges%2C%20among%20whom%20is%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud.%20It%20will%20begin%20hearing%20the%20cases%20on%20September%2020.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22